data.enText: a copy of a document, etc. made by the action of light on a specially treated surface

data.chText: 你需要多少复印件就复印多少吧。
data.enText: Make as many photocopies as you need.
to make a photocopy of sth

data.chText: 你能不能在5点钟前把这些给我复印好？
data.enText: Can you get these photocopied for me by 5 o'clock?

data.chText: 我这一天的大部分时间似乎都花在复印上了。
data.enText: I seem to have spent most of the day photocopying.

data.chText: 用铅笔写的评语没有复印清楚。
data.enText: The comments in pencil haven't photocopied very well.

tr: a photographic copy of written or printed or graphic work

value.def: A photocopy is a copy of a document made using a photocopier.
If you photocopy a document, you make a copy of it using a photocopier.

example.ex: Staff photocopied the cheque before cashing it.
example.tran: 员工在兑现前复印了支票。
